Preface: - Mauje Kuwarbannav Ganeshnagar, Ta. The Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zilla Parishad, Ratnagiri has accorded technical approval to the original budget under the order No. (2) in respect of the budget for the Correctional Re-connection Tap Water Supply Scheme at Ratnagiri, ZP. Also, the original administrative approval for the scheme has been granted under the order in reference No. (9). Accordingly, the Chief Executive Officer, Zilla Parishad, Ratnagiri has submitted a proposal to the Government under letter no. (3) under reference for grant of revised administrative approval to the existing tap water supply scheme on account of increase in the cost of the scheme on account of overcharging tender. The Government was under consideration to grant revised administrative approval to the price subject to the revised technical approval granted by the competent authorities under Order No. (4).

The revised administrative approval is being granted subject to the following conditions for a nominal price of Rs.385 / - (Rupees Two Crore Twenty Seven Lakh Ninety Six Thousand Three Hundred and Eighty Five only).
Conditions
The Chief Executive Officer / Chief Engineer will be responsible for completing all the remaining works within the prescribed time frame at the above mentioned revised cost.
The original administrative approval agreed upon for the scheme as well as the terms and conditions mentioned while granting the technical approval should be strictly adhered to.

Once the scheme is completed, it should be handed over to the concerned Gram Panchayat. The concerned Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad shall be responsible for taking over the scheme within one month from the date of receipt of STATA notification that the scheme has been actually completed by the concerned Executive Engineer, Rural Water Supply Department, Zila Parishad.

Immediately after the actual completion of the scheme, a joint inspection of the scheme should be conducted by the concerned Executive Engineer, Zilla Parishad and concerned Gram Panchayat officials and if any defects are found in the ST inspection, they should be corrected before handing over the scheme.

The Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad concerned shall not receive any assistance from the Government for meeting the recurring expenditure incurred annually for implementation, maintenance, repairs (including special modifications), depreciation in the scheme or renovation of machinery.
On completion of the scheme, it is mandatory for the local body (concerned Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad) to transfer the scheme. The accounts of the scheme should also be closed.

According to a CAG report in 2013, 21% of the water supply schemes in the state have been shut down due to lack of maintenance and non-payment of electricity charges. In this case, the Gram Panchayat / Zilla Parishad concerned will be responsible for increasing the water tariff as per the requirement in order to make the scheme financially viable.
7. Action should be taken in accordance with the prevailing policy on corruption.
The District Council shall be responsible for ensuring that the present scheme is not revised under any circumstances.
9. Administrative expenses are not admissible under Jal Jeevan FR if the scheme is modified.

The amount should be shared between the Centre and the states as per the guidelines. Also, as per the revised administrative approval, the discovered / approved cost is subtracted from the approved cost and the remaining cost is water life.
